<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Good Post (NT)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:12 p.m. 28/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Good Post (NT)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1968" TARGET=_self>Re: lack of melee on pvp server</A> (Stupid)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I play a Paladin on the side. My primary character is a Troll

<BR>&gt; Shaman, but when I get tired of sitting and meditating all the
<BR>&gt; time I switch to the Paladin. And you know what? You're
<BR>&gt; absolutely right. Paladins do rock, but you really have to be a
<BR>&gt; lot more careful with them. The "lay hands" thing is
<BR>&gt; only good once each day (about every 90 minutes realtime) so it
<BR>&gt; is not to be used lightly. I think I've used it twice so far,
<BR>&gt; total. Each time it was a life-or-death situation. And it
<BR>&gt; surprised the hell out of at least one silly Dark Elf
<BR>&gt; Necromancer that took me for an easy kill!!
<P>&gt; I will say this: playing a Paladin requires a lot more
<BR>&gt; "finesse" than a spellcaster. Until you reach level
<BR>&gt; nine, you're so much cannon fodder. In contrast, a Necromancer
<BR>&gt; (which seems to be a REALLY popular class) is a virtual killing
<BR>&gt; machine by the time they reach level four. Of course, by the
<BR>&gt; time they reach ten or so, THEY are cannon fodder, so it all
<BR>&gt; evens out.
<P>&gt; God help me if/when I get a Holy Sword. I'll be hooked for life.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
